A vintage-style illustration of two intricate mechanical blueprints laid side by side on aged parchment paper, one showing an ornate clockwork mechanism with all its gears and springs exposed and labeled with measurement lines, the other showing a similar clock but encased in a mysterious black box with only input and output arrows visible. Golden compass tools, brass calipers, and antique drafting instruments scattered around the edges. Warm sepia tones with deep burgundy and navy accents, reminiscent of Victorian-era technical drawings. The blueprints have coffee stains and slightly curled corners, illuminated by soft candlelight casting gentle shadows across the textured paper surface.
